miniBio.en-US: Family Ministry Pastor - Preston Trail Community Church, Frisco, TX

quote.en-US: Healthy families are a big deal for all of us. At Preston Trail our 'one word' to describe who we are as a church and the primary center of our ministry, is 'FAMILY'. After hours of research we concluded that the number one way we could serve our community was to offer a well-balanced and vibrant marriage ministry. We already had a good start to building a strong marriage ministry, but knew there was more we wanted to offer. When we heard about the MMTC, we went curious and came away excited believing we had found the missing piece of our marriage ministry puzzle. The team at Watermark is like family to us, they are one of the most Kingdom-minded ministries that we have the pleasure of partnering with… they share what they’ve developed over years of trial and error, are available to talk, and walk alongside other churches as they begin ministering to couples. What they offer is a huge gift to the Church!

miniBio.en-US: Leadership Network, Co-author of the Externally Focused Church and To Transform a City

quote.en-US: One of the biggest ‘white spaces’ on the missional map of the church is helping marriages and relationships thrive—both in the church and in the community. But precious few churches really know what to do to build healthy and growing marriages. Watermark’s Marriage Ministry Training Conference is a motivational, practical, and scalable approach to church-based marriage ministry. You will come away with a vision and a plan.

body.en-US:
The [Westin Park Central](http://www.westindallasparkcentral.com/) is within walking distance to the church. To make a reservation at the Westin for this conference, you can [book online](http://www.starwoodhotels.com/westin/rates/rate.html?propertyID=472&rp=SN:430499,,,&language=en_US&EM=oneclickURL_430499_SETWATWD_BOOK_WI_472_NAD).

The Residence Inn Park Central is also within walking distance to the church. To make a reservation at The Residence Inn, you can call (972) 503-1333. Be sure to mention you are with Watermark’s Marriage Ministry Training Conference.

[Learn more about Watermark’s location](http://www.watermark.org/dallas/about/contact-us).

IMPORTANT NOTE:
The Marriage Ministry Training Conference is open to any church who is looking to start or improve their marriage ministry. However, in order to use the Watermark marriage ministry materials you must agree with these [doctrinal beliefs](http://marriagehelp.org/statement-of-faith "Statement of Faith").

Watermark Community Church will be hosting a Marriage Ministry Training Conference for all church leaders (staff and lay leaders) who would like to get an inside look at working marriage ministry models. Whether you don't know where to begin your marriage ministry, would like to improve what you are already doing, or would like to revitalize your church marriage ministry, then come join us.

Our next Marriage Ministry Training Conference will be on October 17-18, 2018. Registration will open in May of 2018.
